cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper is about weakly supervised semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a large scale co-segmentation framework, which involves clustering and grouping similar objects in images, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves training a network using image-level labels, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper retrieves images from search engines, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and uses natural language queries, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
